resources.string:
Source and Demo code at https://github.com/danielemaddaluno/Android-Update-Checker

To use the Update Checker automatically, you can call from the onCreate() of your activity the following code line, which will test for updates automatically once a day:
new UpdateRunnable(this, new Handler()).start();

Otherwise if the Update Check is requested by a user action you can call the following code line (you can test this function by clicking the button below):
new UpdateRunnable(this, new Handler()).force(true).start();
